Police in Naivasha have shot dead three suspected carjackers who included a woman following a series of highway robberies in the last one month. 
The three youthful were shot dead near Naivasha slaughterhouse located along the Nairobi Nakuru highway moments after carjacking a group of passengers and robbing them. 
Three other suspects managed to escape. Police have recovered mobile phones and other effects stolen from the passengers. 
The Saturday evening incident came a day after another group of passengers were robbed on the same highway while on their way to Nairobi. Naivasha Deputy OCPD John Kwasa said that they suspected that the group was behind a series of robberies along the highway.